WEBVTT

00:03.204 --> 00:05.471
            [ Sighs ]

00:07.000 --> 00:13.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:30.631 --> 00:33.232
            [ Groans ]

00:40.741 --> 00:43.342
                  Acting up?

00:43.344 --> 00:45.744
     Yeah, my --
  my Twix is stuck.

00:47.281 --> 00:51.250
                 Yeah,
       they're tricky sometimes.

00:54.455 --> 00:56.555
                Gets hung up
           on the little ridges.

00:56.557 --> 00:57.623
                   Ridges?

00:59.660 --> 01:01.460
          On the chocolate part.

01:04.799 --> 01:06.632
               Son of a bitch.

01:08.569 --> 01:11.103
   Don't report me.

01:11.105 --> 01:13.439
      [ Grunts ]

01:13.441 --> 01:16.075
 Desperate measures.

01:21.615 --> 01:23.148
       They finally called back.

01:24.318 --> 01:25.417
               And?

01:25.419 --> 01:27.619
                  Evidently
               it was too late.

01:27.621 --> 01:29.321
    What do you mean too late?

01:29.323 --> 01:32.791
Ms. person said the deal
had already gone through.

01:32.793 --> 01:35.260
      I got a call for you,
             sheriff.

01:35.262 --> 01:36.795
Be there in a minute.

01:37.731 --> 01:40.833
    The judge already signed off
          on it, I guess.

01:40.835 --> 01:44.136
    What? didn't the senator try
            and stop it?

01:44.138 --> 01:47.172
     I don't know
any of the details, Ted.

01:47.174 --> 01:51.276
   Just that it's,
you know, a done deal.

01:51.278 --> 01:52.878
                 A done deal.

01:52.880 --> 01:54.446
      Evidently.

02:01.288 --> 02:02.788
              So, what, Daniel
           just leaves town now?

02:02.790 --> 02:05.390
As a convicted murderer,
      but yeah.

02:05.392 --> 02:06.391
                  How long?

02:06.393 --> 02:07.392
        What?

02:07.394 --> 02:08.560
              Before he leaves.

02:08.562 --> 02:10.729
      He'd have
a certain amount of time

02:10.731 --> 02:12.664
  To get his affairs
      in order.

02:12.666 --> 02:13.732
                What affairs?

02:13.734 --> 02:16.335
About 30 days, I think.

02:19.773 --> 02:21.306
      So what do you want to do?

02:22.276 --> 02:23.509
              What?

02:23.511 --> 02:25.144
              You still want to
                press charges?

02:26.247 --> 02:29.715
  I didn't want to press charges
       in the first place.

02:38.559 --> 02:42.194
           [ Scraping ]

03:12.626 --> 03:14.493
               It's over, Ted.

03:17.631 --> 03:18.797
                 That right?

03:18.799 --> 03:21.600
                 I'll be
          out of your hair soon.

03:21.602 --> 03:23.502
                  On my way.

03:23.504 --> 03:27.506
              Your mother's gone
              to get some food.

03:27.508 --> 03:31.376
    Gonna do something for your,
               uh...

03:31.378 --> 03:32.678
         For your deal, I guess.

03:33.514 --> 03:35.647
           That's nice.

03:35.649 --> 03:39.384
             Just her way. food.

03:42.656 --> 03:48.594
I'd like to help finish
the kitchen before I leave, Ted.

03:48.596 --> 03:50.862
   I really would.
you know, do the grunt work.

03:50.864 --> 03:52.931
  Whatever you need.

03:54.468 --> 03:56.802
       Is that
 a possibility, Ted?

03:58.906 --> 04:03.775
    Might be best you just focus
      on your leaving and all.

04:05.746 --> 04:08.747
That's the most important thing,
           isn't it?

04:12.820 --> 04:15.354
 I would say so, Ted.

04:54.862 --> 04:57.829
             Some things
      you just don't see coming.

04:57.831 --> 04:59.831
And then teddy Talbot
      shows up.

04:59.833 --> 05:00.899
     [ Chuckles ]

05:00.901 --> 05:02.701
Just when you don't need him.

05:02.703 --> 05:04.936
            Who was Christopher,
                  senator?

05:04.938 --> 05:06.505
   Who's that, now?

05:06.507 --> 05:07.973
           Daniel said there was
            a Christopher there

05:07.975 --> 05:09.608
      With Hanna and the others.

05:09.610 --> 05:13.645
Well, I suppose he was speaking
of Christopher Nelms,

05:13.647 --> 05:17.716
One of the 40 or so kids
down at the river that night.

05:17.718 --> 05:18.984
                    I see.

05:18.986 --> 05:22.688
Holder’s alleging
that Chris was with Hanna

05:22.690 --> 05:24.890
Was news to me, of course.

05:27.695 --> 05:31.863
Enjoy your victory, Sondra.

05:31.865 --> 05:35.367
This is your conviction,
      not mine.

05:35.369 --> 05:38.403
   You're the d.a.
    of record now.

05:38.405 --> 05:42.407
In fact, if you recall,

05:42.409 --> 05:45.844
I was against the idea
of a plea deal initially.

05:45.846 --> 05:48.580
But you convinced me,
       Sondra.

05:48.582 --> 05:52.584
It was a good call on your part,
  a very good call.

05:52.586 --> 05:54.519
Now we can all move on,
      can't we?

05:56.457 --> 05:58.890
Well, I’m off to Atlanta.

05:58.892 --> 06:01.793
Back to the state's business.

06:01.795 --> 06:03.762
If you want a cheerleader
    in your corner

06:03.764 --> 06:05.130
For your re-election,

06:05.132 --> 06:07.599
I'm just a phone call away.

06:07.601 --> 06:10.369
     That's very kind of you,
             senator.

06:12.439 --> 06:14.506
      During the original trial,

06:14.508 --> 06:16.508
         Holder’s attorney tried
               to introduce

06:16.510 --> 06:20.445
  Hanna's promiscuous reputation
         for the record.

06:20.447 --> 06:22.514
        The judge disallowed it.

06:22.516 --> 06:23.915
Why would a judge do that?

06:23.917 --> 06:26.918
                 Sondra,
          it was rumour, hearsay.

06:26.920 --> 06:30.021
                There was
          no real corroboration.

06:30.023 --> 06:32.924
Who would corroborate having sex
with a 16-year-old girl,

06:32.926 --> 06:34.159
Consensual or otherwise?

06:34.161 --> 06:35.761
                   Exactly.

06:35.763 --> 06:38.997
         We got our man, Sondra.

06:38.999 --> 06:40.999
             Holden admitted it.

06:41.001 --> 06:42.601
                  Twice now.

06:42.603 --> 06:45.570
         If you want to delve
     into that girl's reputation

06:45.572 --> 06:49.174
       Or the reputation
of a now-middle-aged family man,

06:49.176 --> 06:51.042
        Do so at your own peril.

06:51.044 --> 06:53.044
Is that a threat, senator?

06:53.046 --> 06:55.414
                   Hardly.

06:55.416 --> 06:58.850
                I'm done here.

06:58.852 --> 07:02.888
                 As they say,
               I feel complete.

07:02.890 --> 07:05.657
      The peril I’m speaking of,
       madam district attorney,

07:05.659 --> 07:07.626
         Goes with the territory
               of your job

07:07.628 --> 07:10.629
           And the territory
       of where you do your job.

07:10.631 --> 07:13.665
 Is there still peril
for you here, senator?

07:14.868 --> 07:16.601
              Is <I>that a threat,
                 ms. person?

07:19.573 --> 07:21.873
     Just an honest question.

07:21.875 --> 07:25.944
        Life is always perilous.

07:25.946 --> 07:28.847
            That's what gives it
                 its spice.

07:51.772 --> 07:55.774
       Tawney:
 teddy? is that you?

07:55.776 --> 07:57.209
                   Tawney?

07:57.211 --> 07:58.910
                Yeah, it's me.

07:58.912 --> 08:01.213
          I didn't see your car.

08:09.022 --> 08:11.723
             Tawney?

08:35.616 --> 08:38.783
[ Motorcycle engine turns over ]

08:53.300 --> 08:55.867
                  [ Sighs ]

08:55.869 --> 08:57.002
            Bartender:
       what are you having?

08:57.004 --> 08:58.870
            Just a coke, please.

08:58.872 --> 09:00.705
Can I get another PBR?

09:00.707 --> 09:03.208
                     Pb?
       PBR.

09:03.210 --> 09:05.710
                 You do
        have to get out of here.

09:08.315 --> 09:09.948
  I'm all packed up.

09:12.185 --> 09:15.053
I left my keys in the apartment
   on the counter.

09:16.156 --> 09:17.923
         Just like that.

09:17.925 --> 09:20.225
               Just like that.

09:20.227 --> 09:22.594
    You have to travel light
in your line of work, don't you?

09:22.596 --> 09:23.895
You can't have it both ways,
       Amantha.

09:23.897 --> 09:25.564
                   Why not?

09:25.566 --> 09:27.299
Did you sleep with me so I would
represent your brother?

09:27.301 --> 09:29.334
    Did you represent my brother
    so you could sleep with me?

09:29.336 --> 09:33.271
  I asked you first.

09:33.273 --> 09:35.273
              I don't know, John.

09:35.275 --> 09:41.947
         The circumstances were,
          shall we say, unusual.

09:41.949 --> 09:44.349
                It certainly
            wasn't premeditated.

09:44.351 --> 09:46.117
               Or maybe it was.

09:46.119 --> 09:48.687
          It doesn't matter now.

09:48.689 --> 09:52.123
    It does to me.

09:52.125 --> 09:56.094
Did he say he did it?

09:56.096 --> 09:57.762
      The deed?

09:57.764 --> 10:00.665
             Did he say it, John?

10:02.302 --> 10:05.737
    He did say it.

10:10.177 --> 10:11.643
          Then I hope he did it.

10:11.645 --> 10:13.311
       I think
sometimes he believes he did

10:13.313 --> 10:16.281
And sometimes he doesn't.

10:16.283 --> 10:19.651
 I truly don't think
      he knows.

10:19.653 --> 10:21.319
        I'm beginning to wonder.

10:21.321 --> 10:24.222
The one thing I know is
    he needs help.

10:24.224 --> 10:27.292
  He's got one month
before he has to leave.

10:27.294 --> 10:28.760
              What are you now?

10:28.762 --> 10:30.228
           His banishment coach?

10:30.230 --> 10:31.630
   He can't do this
     by himself.

10:31.632 --> 10:33.064
  He's not capable.

10:33.066 --> 10:35.400
       And you can't help those
      who won't help themselves.

10:35.402 --> 10:37.902
       He still
has to live his life.

10:37.904 --> 10:40.372
                So do we all.

10:40.374 --> 10:42.073
                   Hoorah.

10:48.715 --> 10:52.283
  I had this fantasy
that you were gonna come here

10:52.285 --> 10:56.388
And tell me that he decided
not to go through with it.

10:56.390 --> 10:58.356
That he decided to fight.

10:58.358 --> 11:00.425
              I implored him to.

11:00.427 --> 11:02.761
             Up to the very end.

11:02.763 --> 11:05.397
  Good for you, John.

11:14.708 --> 11:16.441
    Does this mean
we're going steady again?

11:16.443 --> 11:18.343
                Probably not.

11:20.781 --> 11:22.981
  I wasn't serious.

11:22.983 --> 11:24.783
     It's gross.

11:29.423 --> 11:33.858
   I can't believe
you went into her room.

11:33.860 --> 11:36.027
                 Me neither.

11:36.029 --> 11:38.129
Was it like they say?

11:38.131 --> 11:40.031
              What do they say?

11:40.033 --> 11:41.733
You know what they say.

11:41.735 --> 11:43.234
             It's like they say.

11:43.236 --> 11:46.071
           Like she'd been there
                 yesterday.

11:47.074 --> 11:48.373
     Sounds sad.

11:48.375 --> 11:50.742
                 It was sad.

11:50.744 --> 11:54.245
Why did you come over here,
        Jared?

11:54.247 --> 11:55.313
   Out of the blue.

11:57.918 --> 11:59.951
       He confessed again today.

11:59.953 --> 12:01.986
        What?

12:01.988 --> 12:05.790
 To killing her, strangling her,
            whatever.

12:07.861 --> 12:09.194
       My god.

12:09.196 --> 12:10.862
       Now he gets to leave town

12:10.864 --> 12:14.232
    While the rest of us have to
      stay here and eat shit.

12:18.472 --> 12:22.373
  I'm sorry, Jared.

12:22.375 --> 12:25.210
             It's cool, I guess.

12:25.212 --> 12:28.880
             I mean, not really.

12:30.317 --> 12:33.118
   He used to like
Willie d's barbecue as a boy.

12:33.120 --> 12:34.352
 I thought it'd be --

12:34.354 --> 12:36.988
      I don't know -- nostalgic.

12:36.990 --> 12:39.057
 Everyday forks okay?

12:39.059 --> 12:42.961
                  [ Sighs ]
              it's take-out, Ted.

12:42.963 --> 12:45.163
Jared said he was going to eat
 at Claire’s tonight.

12:45.165 --> 12:47.132
               Did you tell him
                 he couldn't?

12:47.134 --> 12:49.768
                     No.

12:49.770 --> 12:52.971
    I didn't think
he was seeing Claire any more.

12:52.973 --> 12:56.007
                I don't know.

12:56.009 --> 12:58.810
I called Tawney today.
        twice.

12:58.812 --> 13:00.211
              I don't think
          that'd be a good idea,

13:00.213 --> 13:01.479
       Them coming over tonight,
                 Janet.

13:01.481 --> 13:03.982
  Not to invite them
   to dinner, Ted.

13:03.984 --> 13:06.951
     Just to see
  how she was doing.

13:06.953 --> 13:08.052
                  Of course.

13:08.054 --> 13:09.220
                 How is she?

13:09.222 --> 13:11.790
She didn't return my calls.

13:11.792 --> 13:15.293
                   I'm sure
             she's just resting.

13:15.295 --> 13:20.031
So, just set the table
 for three, I guess.

13:24.371 --> 13:28.473
    You used to like Willie d's,
            didn't you?

13:28.475 --> 13:33.144
    To be honest,
I-i don't remember, mother.

13:33.146 --> 13:37.048
                  Oh.
        well, I thought you did.

13:37.050 --> 13:39.050
      Maybe so.

13:39.052 --> 13:43.154
I just...don't remember.

13:45.158 --> 13:47.058
        Ted: I don't think
 Willie d's has been around here

13:47.060 --> 13:48.927
       For 20 years, Janet.

13:48.929 --> 13:50.261
                 Willie d's?

13:50.263 --> 13:51.596
           Pretty sure
      Willie didn't start it

13:51.598 --> 13:55.066
     Till he was, uh...gone.

13:57.070 --> 13:58.603
   Why didn't you say something,
                Ted?

13:58.605 --> 14:00.371
              Well,
     you'd already bought it.

14:02.909 --> 14:05.210
     It's tasty.

14:07.347 --> 14:09.113
   Mmm. real tasty.

14:11.451 --> 14:15.453
I am glad to have had
the experience of Willie d's.

14:15.455 --> 14:16.855
  Thank you, mother.

14:19.226 --> 14:20.592
             Amantha had to work
                   tonight.

14:20.594 --> 14:21.993
      That's why she's not here.

14:21.995 --> 14:24.128
 She seems committed.

14:24.130 --> 14:25.463
                Thrifty town.

14:25.465 --> 14:27.899
         Didn't see that coming.

14:31.638 --> 14:33.438
    Where's Jared?

14:33.440 --> 14:36.441
             Oh, he is
   at his friend Claire’s house.

14:36.443 --> 14:38.977
        I see.

14:38.979 --> 14:40.311
     It had already been planned

14:40.313 --> 14:42.513
        For them to get together
           tonight, so, um...

14:42.515 --> 14:47.485
          Studying or something.

14:47.487 --> 14:51.956
I like Jared, mother.

14:51.958 --> 14:56.361
You and Ted have done
   a...a great job.

14:58.398 --> 15:00.164
          All my kids are great.

15:00.166 --> 15:03.067
        [ Knock on door ]

15:10.543 --> 15:14.445
                   Teddy.
           what a nice surprise.

15:20.553 --> 15:22.120
                 You hungry?

15:26.593 --> 15:29.327
         Just had to come
           for a visit.

15:29.329 --> 15:33.598
     See everybody, I guess.

15:33.600 --> 15:35.099
           That's so thoughtful.

15:35.101 --> 15:36.501
         Let me get you a plate.

15:36.503 --> 15:40.138
               Oh, I’m fine.
           I just had leftovers.

15:40.140 --> 15:42.473
             Please.
 you like Willie d's, don't you?

15:42.475 --> 15:46.344
             You know I do.
        it's my favourite, Janet.

15:54.554 --> 15:57.021
                 Hello, dad.

15:57.023 --> 15:58.323
                    Son.

16:02.062 --> 16:04.996
                         Daniel.

16:04.998 --> 16:06.497
     Hello, Ted.

16:12.439 --> 16:14.205
          How's Tawney doing?

16:14.207 --> 16:16.207
                   She's hanging
                     in there.

16:16.209 --> 16:18.710
               Um, we haven't
              told Daniel yet.

16:18.712 --> 16:22.013
              Uh, just so much
           going on around here.

16:22.015 --> 16:23.348
                  Oh, yeah.

16:23.350 --> 16:26.150
          I heard the good news.

16:26.152 --> 16:28.252
               Congratulations.

16:30.323 --> 16:32.090
   Thank you, Ted.

16:33.326 --> 16:36.394
       Tawney had a miscarriage.

16:36.396 --> 16:39.030
     I'm terribly sorry, Ted.

16:39.032 --> 16:41.199
               Sorry for what?

16:41.201 --> 16:44.002
            Your loss.

16:50.610 --> 16:53.211
              I sure do love me
               some Willie d's.

16:53.213 --> 16:58.182
       I remember the first time
              we all went.

16:58.184 --> 17:01.252
                  Me, you,
            and dad and Amantha.

17:01.254 --> 17:04.388
        That was the first time?

17:04.391 --> 17:06.523
    It was for me.

17:10.063 --> 17:12.730
       [ Insects chirping ]

17:23.276 --> 17:25.810
    Hello, miss -- miss Kathy?

17:25.811 --> 17:28.413
           It's Tawney.

17:28.415 --> 17:32.750
   I...I hope I haven't called
          at a bad time.

17:32.752 --> 17:36.220
             Oh, yes,
      I remember meal time.

17:36.222 --> 17:38.756
    Um, I can call back later.

17:38.758 --> 17:41.125
        No, no emergency.

17:41.127 --> 17:45.797
   Um, I just -- I thought that
   I might come by for a visit.

17:45.799 --> 17:48.266
   You know, come and see you.

17:48.268 --> 17:50.301
      Maybe stay a few days.

17:52.305 --> 17:55.473
      This week's not good?

17:55.475 --> 17:57.642
            Next week?

17:57.644 --> 17:59.610
            Of course.
     that -- that could work.

18:01.614 --> 18:03.314
              Uh...

18:03.316 --> 18:05.550
     Oh, e-everything's fine.

18:09.456 --> 18:12.356
           Yes, ma'am.
         I feel blessed.

18:13.493 --> 18:14.692
         All right, then.

18:14.694 --> 18:17.261
             You too.

18:36.516 --> 18:39.484
             Well, I guess
       I better be getting back.

18:39.486 --> 18:43.754
        Well,
let me fix Tawney a plate.

18:43.756 --> 18:46.457
                Sure. why not?

18:48.194 --> 18:49.560
               Maybe she's got
              her appetite back.

18:59.506 --> 19:01.339
      Can I have a word with you
             in private?

19:02.842 --> 19:04.509
      Sure, Ted.

19:21.194 --> 19:23.427
       You know
  where my wife is?

19:23.429 --> 19:25.229
                I don't, Ted.

19:25.231 --> 19:26.531
But you did, didn't you?

19:26.533 --> 19:28.566
            That is true. I did.

19:30.336 --> 19:32.703
Why'd you tell her that?

19:32.705 --> 19:34.305
         Why?

19:35.308 --> 19:37.808
                I don't know.

19:37.810 --> 19:44.382
          She was confused
   about her situation, and I...

19:44.384 --> 19:50.755
     I felt that telling her
  might help her clarify things.

19:50.757 --> 19:52.256
       As what?

19:52.258 --> 19:54.559
Whether to leave me or not?

19:54.561 --> 19:57.295
                 Or to stay.

19:57.297 --> 20:01.666
Probably felt good to unburden
yourself, too, didn't it?

20:01.668 --> 20:04.535
 Confess your crime,
     so to speak.

20:04.537 --> 20:05.870
               Perhaps it did.

20:05.872 --> 20:07.271
                I don't know.

20:07.273 --> 20:10.408
I think the real reason
    you did it...

20:10.410 --> 20:14.478
  Is 'cause you knew
she'd probably find out one day.

20:14.480 --> 20:16.380
 But if you told her
      yourself,

20:16.382 --> 20:18.549
You could put your spin on it
       somehow.

20:18.551 --> 20:20.618
         There was no spin, Ted.

20:20.620 --> 20:22.787
       Really?

20:22.789 --> 20:26.524
When it comes down to it,
     you told her

20:26.526 --> 20:29.527
Because you knew that was
your best chance of having her.

20:29.529 --> 20:30.595
      Wasn't it?

20:30.597 --> 20:32.496
    For yourself.

20:32.498 --> 20:34.398
      Admit it.

20:35.969 --> 20:37.635
            That's not possible.

20:37.637 --> 20:39.904
     What isn't?

20:39.906 --> 20:41.539
                  She and I.

20:43.009 --> 20:46.978
    If I find out
  you are with her,

20:46.980 --> 20:48.846
I'm gonna press charges.

20:48.848 --> 20:50.648
   I swear to god.

20:51.985 --> 20:55.987
It'd be worth the humiliation
to see you back in that box

20:55.989 --> 20:58.723
 Where you can't hurt
    anybody else.

21:10.003 --> 21:12.403
Carl: sorry to interrupt
     your dinner.

21:12.405 --> 21:13.804
      It wasn't very appetizing.

21:13.806 --> 21:16.607
State medical examiner's
coming in the morning.

21:16.609 --> 21:18.342
They'll check dental records,

21:18.344 --> 21:20.878
But there's still enough
of George Melton left

21:20.880 --> 21:22.913
    In that corpse
  for me to be sure.

21:22.915 --> 21:25.549
         We got to do everything
          by the book, sheriff.

21:25.551 --> 21:27.318
     I know that.

21:27.320 --> 21:30.054
I'm just saying, that's George,
as sure as I’m standing here.

21:30.056 --> 21:32.323
      Are you also saying that's
      a bullet hole in his head?

21:32.325 --> 21:34.025
 Sure looks like one.

21:36.996 --> 21:41.065
            [ Sighs ]
  don't suppose you found a gun?

21:41.067 --> 21:42.533
       Not yet.

21:42.535 --> 21:46.370
GBI’s gonna send divers
   in the morning.

21:49.809 --> 21:51.075
     Ms. person.

21:52.512 --> 21:54.445
I don't have an agenda.

21:55.448 --> 21:57.081
   That's a good place to start,
              sheriff.

21:57.083 --> 22:00.351
No, I mean I don't plan
to confer with the senator

22:00.353 --> 22:01.752
About the investigation.

22:01.754 --> 22:03.721
             How's he gonna feel
                 about that?

22:03.723 --> 22:05.956
 That's his business.

22:05.958 --> 22:07.591
     This isn't.

22:10.930 --> 22:12.863
              [ Sighs ]
     did they find George’s car?

22:14.600 --> 22:16.734
         No.

22:16.736 --> 22:18.336
   No, they didn't.

22:19.605 --> 22:20.705
                 What is it?

22:23.910 --> 22:28.646
I...talked to George’s father
   a few days ago.

22:28.648 --> 22:32.116
He said George had been
out of sorts for some time now.

22:32.118 --> 22:33.584
                Out of sorts?

22:33.586 --> 22:36.387
      Depressed,
  I guess you'd say.

22:36.389 --> 22:37.755
                 About what?

22:37.757 --> 22:39.357
  All I’m saying is

22:39.359 --> 22:41.992
      Suicide's
a strong possibility here.

22:42.595 --> 22:45.463
      I never assumed it wasn't.

22:47.100 --> 22:49.100
     Yes, ma'am.

22:51.471 --> 22:53.404
            Good night, sheriff.

22:53.406 --> 22:56.407
     Good night.

22:56.409 --> 22:59.510
       [ Sander whirring ]

23:11.657 --> 23:13.858
        [ Whirring stops ]

23:13.860 --> 23:15.860
      I thought
we had discussed this.

23:15.862 --> 23:17.762
               I'm sorry, Ted.

23:17.764 --> 23:21.599
                I didn't know
               what else to do.

23:23.903 --> 23:26.871
    Well, for one,
you could tell your mother

23:26.873 --> 23:28.606
What you did to teddy.

23:31.711 --> 23:32.710
                  Sure, Ted.

23:32.712 --> 23:34.678
'Cause I’m not gonna do it.

23:34.680 --> 23:36.480
Be put in that position.

23:37.884 --> 23:40.151
                I understand.

23:40.153 --> 23:42.586
 And you can go stay
   with your sister

23:42.588 --> 23:44.989
Until you leave for good.

23:48.661 --> 23:50.594
               No problem, Ted.

23:52.698 --> 23:55.699
    See, Daniel...

23:55.701 --> 23:58.469
     I don't know
what else to do, either.

24:45.885 --> 24:48.786
Everything but a gun.

24:58.698 --> 24:59.864
            He's gone.

24:59.866 --> 25:01.699
                           What?

25:01.701 --> 25:04.268
      He's not in his room.

25:04.270 --> 25:06.070
         Hmm.

25:06.072 --> 25:07.571
          Well, did you see him?

25:07.573 --> 25:11.775
No. not this morning.

25:14.080 --> 25:16.013
He didn't say anything
       to you?

25:16.015 --> 25:17.982
                 About what?

25:20.186 --> 25:22.586
I don't know. about where
he was going, I guess.

25:23.589 --> 25:24.655
                 Not a word.

25:26.125 --> 25:28.192
  I'm sure he's off
on one of his adventures.

25:30.897 --> 25:34.598
                 Well,
        I’m gonna go see Tawney.

25:34.600 --> 25:35.866
  She call you back?

25:35.868 --> 25:39.203
                 She didn't.

25:41.607 --> 25:42.806
             Did you tell Jared?

25:44.911 --> 25:46.176
          Tell me what?

25:46.178 --> 25:48.579
  No, I wasn't sure
  if you wanted to.

25:48.581 --> 25:50.247
             Why would I want to
                  tell him?

25:50.249 --> 25:52.750
     I'm actually right here.

25:52.752 --> 25:55.986
       Tawney had a miscarriage.
          she's lost the baby.

25:55.988 --> 25:57.988
               How?

25:57.990 --> 26:00.057
            These things happen.

26:00.059 --> 26:02.326
                It was early.

26:12.071 --> 26:14.638
   You sleep okay?

26:14.640 --> 26:16.640
                 Well, um...

26:16.642 --> 26:17.675
Yes. stupid question.

26:17.677 --> 26:20.044
Um...how about breakfast?

26:20.046 --> 26:21.645
                  I'm okay.

26:21.647 --> 26:23.180
Tawney, you got to eat.

26:23.182 --> 26:25.115
               Uh, maybe later.

26:25.117 --> 26:27.718
    Here's cereal.
milk's in the fridge.

26:27.720 --> 26:30.888
If you're feeling frisky,
there's bacon and eggs.

26:30.890 --> 26:33.958
           I won't be here long,
                   Beth.

26:33.960 --> 26:37.761
Tawney, you can stay here
 as long as you like.

26:37.763 --> 26:39.196
    Why are we put
    on god's earth

26:39.198 --> 26:41.165
If not to help people in need,
        right?

26:43.970 --> 26:45.836
              [ Voice breaking ]
                   I guess.

26:47.873 --> 26:52.710
And, um, tears are kinda
 the rule around here

26:52.712 --> 26:55.245
Rather than the exception,
 so don't hold back.

26:57.216 --> 26:58.682
    Sister wives.

26:58.684 --> 27:00.217
        Watch it, buster.

27:02.722 --> 27:04.355
   Morning, Tawney.

27:04.357 --> 27:07.291
Mitch, I-i just want you to know
     I won't be here long.

27:07.293 --> 27:09.326
              Okay,
    you can't say that again.

27:09.328 --> 27:11.795
                      I'm sorry.
        two's your limit.

27:11.797 --> 27:15.032
        [ Chuckles ]
        no more apologies, okay?

27:15.034 --> 27:18.102
This one is with you now.

27:18.104 --> 27:21.372
                   I'm just
             a glorified lifter.

27:21.374 --> 27:22.740
      How are you glorified?

27:22.742 --> 27:24.675
                 [ Chuckles ]

27:24.677 --> 27:27.311
Make yourself at home,
      all right?

27:29.081 --> 27:30.781
I'll check in with you later,
        okay?

27:30.783 --> 27:33.283
          Oh, you don't have to.
              I’ll be fine.

27:33.285 --> 27:37.121
I've had two miscarriages.

27:37.123 --> 27:39.056
Maty's really the miracle.

27:39.058 --> 27:41.158
                I didn't know.

27:41.160 --> 27:45.663
Well, um, nobody talks
   about them much.

27:45.665 --> 27:48.132
    But it's a...

27:48.134 --> 27:50.401
   It's a big deal.

27:50.403 --> 27:52.736
                 Yes, it is.

27:52.738 --> 27:56.206
    The second one
finally got us into therapy.

27:56.208 --> 27:57.975
       You and -- you and Mitch?

27:57.977 --> 27:59.877
      [ Laughs ]
   hard to believe.

27:59.879 --> 28:01.812
  We're so perfect,
      aren't we?

28:01.814 --> 28:08.252
Anyway, um, the woman we talked
to, she's -- she's great.

28:08.254 --> 28:10.421
       And sh--
and she's a Christian.

28:10.423 --> 28:12.056
                 That's good.

28:12.058 --> 28:14.725
  I mean, you know,
she's certified and everything.

28:14.727 --> 28:16.026
     [ Chuckles ]

28:16.028 --> 28:17.394
                  I can't --

28:17.396 --> 28:20.064
      Can't see teddy ever going
           into counselling

28:20.066 --> 28:21.799
           To talk about things.

28:21.801 --> 28:24.101
          [ Horn honks ]

28:24.103 --> 28:27.204
 Romantic, ain't he?

28:27.206 --> 28:29.006
Maybe Ted will come around.

28:29.008 --> 28:30.174
   You never know.

28:36.749 --> 28:38.348
           [ Whimpers ]

28:38.350 --> 28:40.951
        [ Doorbell rings ]

28:48.027 --> 28:49.159
                 Hey, teddy.

28:49.161 --> 28:50.828
                  I thought
              you'd be at work.

28:50.830 --> 28:52.463
   Oh, about ready
     to head out.

28:52.465 --> 28:55.165
            Oh. you forgot
      Tawney’s plate last night.

28:57.069 --> 28:58.368
      Oh, right.

28:58.370 --> 28:59.870
                    Uh...

28:59.872 --> 29:01.472
              Tawney hadn't been
             returning my calls,

29:01.474 --> 29:03.841
        So I thought I’d drop in
        and see how she's doing.

29:06.445 --> 29:08.312
   She's not here.

29:09.381 --> 29:11.181
                Where is she?

29:11.183 --> 29:14.818
       Well...

29:14.820 --> 29:16.220
 I don't know, Janet.

29:17.389 --> 29:19.857
                     Oh.

29:19.859 --> 29:22.993
We've been having some troubles,
I guess you might say.

29:22.995 --> 29:26.263
And, uh, losing the baby kind of
brought things to a head.

29:26.265 --> 29:28.532
                Oh, gracious.

29:28.534 --> 29:30.501
                  I'm sorry.

29:32.104 --> 29:33.771
     It happens.

29:35.174 --> 29:37.141
Do you think she might have gone
       to see miss Kathy?

29:39.211 --> 29:40.844
    Your guess is
   as good as mine.

29:40.846 --> 29:44.181
          Well, I-i know this --
          that wherever she is,

29:44.183 --> 29:46.517
      She's gonna come back here
               to you.

29:46.519 --> 29:47.985
                  [ Sighs ]

29:47.987 --> 29:49.920
                And I’m sorry.

29:49.922 --> 29:51.488
      For what?

29:51.490 --> 29:54.458
        Just been so preoccupied
        with other things lately

29:54.460 --> 29:56.827
       That I haven't been there
                for you.

29:56.829 --> 29:59.930
 It's understandable.

29:59.932 --> 30:03.100
                You're my son,
                 too, teddy.

30:03.102 --> 30:04.902
       And I love you very much.

30:07.139 --> 30:09.973
You've always been real good
    to me, Janet.

30:09.975 --> 30:12.009
   I appreciate it.

30:12.011 --> 30:14.478
                   Oh, god.

30:14.480 --> 30:17.414
       I wish I hadn't asked you
           to call me Janet.

30:17.416 --> 30:20.517
      No biggie.

30:25.424 --> 30:27.925
I kinda need to get to work,
      you know.

30:27.927 --> 30:31.461
                I understand.

30:31.463 --> 30:34.965
       Oh, you -- you keep that.

30:34.967 --> 30:37.301
        Sure.

31:20.179 --> 31:23.247
    [ Speaking indistinctly ]

31:23.249 --> 31:25.649
            [ Laughs ]

31:37.062 --> 31:38.595
       Nice to be outside,
            isn't it?

31:40.266 --> 31:42.232
              It is.

31:42.234 --> 31:46.303
          Parks are one
  of our better ideas, I think.

31:46.305 --> 31:48.305
            We humans.

31:52.912 --> 31:57.314
     I'm...nobody
 to be worried about.

31:57.316 --> 31:59.416
                    Okay.

31:59.418 --> 32:02.920
  I mean -- I mean,
 I came here to read.

32:02.922 --> 32:04.922
Th-that's why I’m here.

32:04.924 --> 32:06.423
  J-j-just to read.

32:07.626 --> 32:09.192
                  It's nice.

32:09.194 --> 32:15.098
I never really read outside,
  underneath the...

32:15.100 --> 32:17.935
  The big blue sky.

32:20.372 --> 32:22.940
It's almost too much.

32:28.414 --> 32:30.180
                 Well, um...

32:30.182 --> 32:32.449
               Have a nice day.

32:37.556 --> 32:40.324
         Yes.

32:40.326 --> 32:42.359
   Have a nice day.

32:42.361 --> 32:47.431
    Whoo-whoo-whoo-whoo-whoo!

32:59.411 --> 33:00.978
              Wynn: have a seat.

33:00.980 --> 33:04.381
        Okay.

33:04.383 --> 33:05.615
                  [ Sighs ]

33:05.617 --> 33:09.653
           Thanks for opening up
               this morning.

33:09.655 --> 33:11.221
      Of course.

33:11.223 --> 33:12.489
       Any time.

33:12.491 --> 33:16.126
              Something came up,
                  you know.

33:16.128 --> 33:17.260
                 [ Chuckles ]

33:17.262 --> 33:19.730
                    Life.

33:19.732 --> 33:23.300
   Everything okay?

33:23.302 --> 33:27.504
       Sometimes it's just nice
     to have a place to come to.

33:27.506 --> 33:29.072
     Heard that.

33:29.074 --> 33:30.507
                 [ Chuckles ]

33:30.509 --> 33:33.310
            Peanut's coming back
                 next week.

33:33.312 --> 33:35.178
         Oh.

33:35.180 --> 33:37.080
             You ever think
       of going back to college?

33:37.082 --> 33:38.582
       College?

33:38.584 --> 33:40.784
    I don't know.

33:40.786 --> 33:42.686
          What about management?

33:42.688 --> 33:43.687
        What?

33:43.689 --> 33:45.455
                    Here.

33:46.525 --> 33:48.225
        Uh...

33:48.227 --> 33:50.660
     Sorry to throw three curves
        at you right in a row.

33:50.662 --> 33:53.397
        Four.
you started with a compliment.

33:55.267 --> 33:57.100
             I can't keep you
         unless I tell corporate

33:57.102 --> 33:58.435
                  You're
         a managerial candidate.

33:58.437 --> 34:00.504
        I see.

34:00.506 --> 34:03.373
    Then they'll let me carry
  an extra associate for a time.

34:05.077 --> 34:06.476
       So am I?

34:06.478 --> 34:08.445
     A candidate.

34:08.447 --> 34:09.579
                I don't know.

34:09.581 --> 34:11.081
                Peanut's not.

34:11.083 --> 34:14.317
          She's found her place,
               so to speak.

34:14.319 --> 34:17.320
     And this is just a stopover
             for Alesha.

34:17.322 --> 34:19.656
                   But you?

34:19.658 --> 34:21.625
                I'm not sure.

34:21.627 --> 34:25.295
      Me either.

34:25.297 --> 34:28.565
          Amantha, I don't think
              anybody dreams

34:28.567 --> 34:30.766
              Of being a manager
               at thrifty town.

34:30.768 --> 34:32.803
              But life happens,

34:32.804 --> 34:37.206
           And, well, there are
         worse places to end up.

34:40.112 --> 34:43.080
               Think about it.

34:43.081 --> 34:45.614
      [ Telephone ringing ]

34:51.190 --> 34:52.322
       Paulie tire and rim.

34:52.324 --> 34:55.859
        Just...just checking in.

34:59.264 --> 35:00.597
     Checking in?

35:00.599 --> 35:03.166
    Let you know I was all right
          and everything.

35:03.168 --> 35:05.735
 That's good to know.

35:05.737 --> 35:07.871
                How about you?

35:07.873 --> 35:10.674
  Me? oh, you know.

35:10.676 --> 35:12.609
Keeping my head down.

35:12.611 --> 35:16.379
               That's probably
             a good thing to do.

35:16.381 --> 35:19.850
Janet came by the house
    this morning.

35:19.852 --> 35:21.118
                  Oh, yeah?

35:21.120 --> 35:23.253
   Said she's been
     calling you.

35:24.456 --> 35:27.224
                Just couldn't
                call her back.

35:27.226 --> 35:28.792
              Not yet, you know.

35:28.794 --> 35:30.861
Well, I had to tell her
      something.

35:30.863 --> 35:32.896
         What -- what'd you say?

35:32.898 --> 35:36.500
      You know,
that we're having problems.

35:36.502 --> 35:38.568
   Marital problems
     or whatever.

35:38.570 --> 35:41.138
                 Sounds good.

35:41.140 --> 35:44.574
            You know,
 the right thing to say for now.

35:45.477 --> 35:47.177
  Can I at least ask
    where you are?

35:49.581 --> 35:51.548
                    Sure.

35:51.550 --> 35:53.650
                  At Beth’s.

35:53.652 --> 35:54.718
     And Mitch’s?

35:54.720 --> 35:55.785
                    Yeah.

35:55.787 --> 35:57.521
    That's just
right down the road.

35:57.523 --> 36:00.357
              It's not that far.

36:00.359 --> 36:03.760
      I might go to miss Kathy’s
              next week.

36:03.762 --> 36:07.464
      Next week?

36:07.466 --> 36:10.400
            I don't know. maybe.

36:10.402 --> 36:12.536
Why don't you just come home,
       Tawney?

36:13.438 --> 36:14.871
                    Teddy.

36:14.873 --> 36:17.874
We can stay in different rooms
for a while or whatever.

36:17.876 --> 36:20.710
             It's not that easy.

36:20.712 --> 36:22.212
       Why not?

36:22.214 --> 36:25.849
          I just need some time,
                  teddy.

36:25.851 --> 36:27.617
So you're coming back?

36:27.619 --> 36:30.453
             I don't know. um...

36:30.455 --> 36:32.589
                  Probably.

36:32.591 --> 36:33.957
                     Yes.

36:35.961 --> 36:38.395
     Yeah, right.

36:41.300 --> 36:44.734
    Beth said she and, um, Mitch
     saw this lady for a while.

36:49.474 --> 36:52.058
      What lady?

36:52.059 --> 36:54.643
            A counsellor.
    marriage counsellor, I guess.

36:54.646 --> 36:58.582
     Said she really helped them
      through some rough times.

37:00.986 --> 37:03.253
You didn't tell them anything,
       did you?

37:03.255 --> 37:06.456
          No. no, of course not.

37:06.458 --> 37:10.527
         I mean, I-i-i told them
          about the miscarriage,

37:10.529 --> 37:13.763
                But, um,
        none of the other stuff.

37:13.765 --> 37:16.299
                 God, teddy.

37:16.301 --> 37:17.801
        Okay.

37:17.803 --> 37:19.502
             I wouldn't do that.

37:19.504 --> 37:21.605
        Okay.
Mitch is just a blabbermouth.

37:21.607 --> 37:23.607
                Well,
     they've been through a lot.

37:23.609 --> 37:27.811
       They had two miscarriages
              before Maty.

37:29.615 --> 37:31.414
    Good for them.

37:31.416 --> 37:33.617
                    What?

37:33.619 --> 37:36.920
Nothing. look, I, uh,
I got a customer, so...

37:36.922 --> 37:40.257
                Oh. oh, okay.

37:40.259 --> 37:41.825
        Okay.
thanks for checking in.

37:41.827 --> 37:45.295
       [ Telephone beeps ]

37:51.837 --> 37:54.938
   We've never gotten this far,
         have we, buddy?

37:54.940 --> 37:58.508
             I mean,
   we've never been over here.

37:58.510 --> 38:00.510
         The final stop.

38:00.512 --> 38:03.380
     Maybe this is our time.

38:03.382 --> 38:06.650
          Maybe this is
          the easy part.

38:06.652 --> 38:09.953
    You know, the letting go.

38:09.955 --> 38:12.055
    It'd be out of our hands.

38:12.057 --> 38:13.690
              Well,
    except for the last words.

38:13.692 --> 38:15.625
        You thought about
      what we're gonna say?

38:15.627 --> 38:17.894
      That's some pressure.

38:17.896 --> 38:19.496
       How many people know

38:19.498 --> 38:22.332
  Their last words are gonna be
        their last words?

38:22.334 --> 38:24.501
       Will mother be here?

38:24.503 --> 38:25.702
              Shit.

38:25.704 --> 38:27.070
    You never know about her.

38:27.072 --> 38:29.039
     She's liable to show up
        for the real deal.

38:29.041 --> 38:31.741
      That would be macabre.

38:31.743 --> 38:33.910
          Hello, mother.

38:33.912 --> 38:35.512
           Hello, son.

38:35.514 --> 38:36.846
         Goodbye, mother.

38:36.848 --> 38:38.381
          Goodbye, son.

38:40.018 --> 38:43.553
             I mean,
     you gotta laugh, right?

38:43.555 --> 38:47.657
      Ah, hell, it probably
       won't happen. again.

38:47.659 --> 38:49.993
    Just like last time, hmm?

38:49.995 --> 38:52.729
    And the time before that.

38:52.731 --> 38:58.768
         It's just a game
      that has to play out.

38:58.770 --> 39:03.340
     Over and over and over.

39:03.342 --> 39:05.408
      But that's the thing.

39:05.410 --> 39:08.978
 You never really know for sure,
              do ya?

39:08.980 --> 39:10.880
           Not really.

39:15.821 --> 39:21.524
    Do we really just want to
     get it over with anyway?

39:21.526 --> 39:27.764
        I mean, deep down.

39:27.766 --> 39:34.838
   'Cause when you're in here,
         all strapped in,

39:35.006 --> 39:38.975
        Ready for take-off,

39:38.977 --> 39:41.444
        Just go to sleep,

39:41.446 --> 39:44.981
    Never wake up ever again.

39:47.786 --> 39:50.820
        You know my vote.

39:50.822 --> 39:52.956
          [ Door opens ]

39:53.692 --> 39:56.126
 Amantha: were you gonna sit out
         here all night?

39:56.128 --> 39:58.395
       [ Lighter flicking ]

39:58.397 --> 39:59.763
          I don't know.

39:59.765 --> 40:02.665
       I drank
a whole bottle of wine

40:02.667 --> 40:05.034
   Waiting for you
to knock on the door.

40:06.171 --> 40:08.772
              Sounds productive.

40:13.078 --> 40:15.512
                  [ Sighs ]

40:20.752 --> 40:22.919
       Amantha.

40:22.921 --> 40:26.489
                     Yes?

40:26.491 --> 40:29.959
      You think
it would be all right if I...

40:29.961 --> 40:32.695
Stayed for a little while?

40:35.867 --> 40:38.034
If you're not comfortable
   with it, just...

40:38.036 --> 40:39.936
                  [ Sighs ]

40:39.938 --> 40:42.439
    I understand.

40:42.441 --> 40:45.942
              Where would you go
                  otherwise?

40:45.944 --> 40:48.578
                Back to mom's?

40:48.580 --> 40:49.612
    I don't know.

40:49.614 --> 40:51.548
 Probably not there.

40:51.550 --> 40:56.152
         I can't be your keeper,
                 Daniel.

40:58.190 --> 40:59.823
        Okay.

40:59.825 --> 41:02.091
              Just doesn't work.

41:02.093 --> 41:04.461
              For either of us.

41:04.463 --> 41:05.995
    I understand.

41:05.997 --> 41:09.032
           I'm not saying to go,
                  Daniel.

41:09.034 --> 41:11.000
         Of course you can stay.

41:11.002 --> 41:12.202
                  Of course.

41:15.474 --> 41:19.609
       But I can't make you care
             about things.

41:19.611 --> 41:22.612
      I can't even make myself
    care about things right now.

41:26.151 --> 41:27.584
I'm sorry to hear that.

41:27.586 --> 41:31.821
       And I can't make you try,
                either.

41:31.823 --> 41:34.157
              It's gonna have to
                come from you.

41:37.796 --> 41:41.130
Well, I’ll try to try.

41:46.037 --> 41:49.105
    [ Sighs ] I got a spare room
      and a blow-up mattress.

41:49.107 --> 41:51.207
    Nothing fancy.

41:51.209 --> 41:53.109
               Sounds perfect.

41:53.111 --> 41:57.013
 I'll go blow it up.

42:05.891 --> 42:07.223
       Where is everybody?

42:07.225 --> 42:09.859
    Grand opening
 at the olive garden.

42:09.861 --> 42:13.096
          Shit. is that tonight?

42:13.098 --> 42:14.531
                   I think
             I made that happen.

42:14.533 --> 42:15.932
              I can't remember.

42:15.934 --> 42:18.768
              Isn't that funny?

42:18.770 --> 42:22.005
Either way, I got to go by there
   and shake some fat hands.

42:22.007 --> 42:23.740
                That gets old.

42:26.211 --> 42:28.645
          Are we through, Marcy?

42:30.315 --> 42:31.881
 I think so, senator.

42:31.883 --> 42:33.917
              Something I said?

42:35.320 --> 42:36.986
      Probably.

42:36.988 --> 42:40.790
                   Well...

42:40.792 --> 42:43.159
           All good things must
         dwarp dee call mush no.

42:43.161 --> 42:44.761
         Hmm?

